rsonal and intimate, Re-Orienting China guides us towards cross-cultural relationships that are critical in today's globalized world.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aAmericansxHistoryx20th centuryxChina. 0aAmericanszChinaxHistoryy20th century. 0aCanadiansxHistoryx20th centuryxChina. 0aCanadianszChinaxHistoryy20th century. 0aTravelers' writings, AmericanxHistory and criticismxChina. 0aTravelers' writings, AmericanzChinaxHistory and criticism. 0aTravelers' writings, Canadian (English)xHistory and criticismxChina. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / Asian / Chinese.2bisacsh  aCommunist.  aOrientalism.  acultural connection.  atravel writing.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Complete eBook-Package 2016z978311127380808iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Upgrade eBook-Package 2016z978311127630440uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978088977441440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780889774414423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780889774414/original  a978-3-11-127380-8  ACUP Complete eBook-Package 2016b2016  a978-3-11-127630-4  ACUP Upgrade eBook-Package 2016b2016  aGBV-deGruyter-alles